Harvey Albert BLOW v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7363. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. June 24, 1963. Stanley J. Walter, Lakewood, Colo., for appellant. John Quinn, U. S. Atty., Albuquerque, N. M., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed June 24, 1963, on the ground that the notice of appeal was not timely filed.
